Abstract = {Open Multi-Agent Systems (MASs) represent a paradigm in which multiple
   autonomous agents communicate and collaborate to achieve shared
   objectives in an open and dynamic environment. These systems require
   specific software engineering capabilities. In the realm of software
   validation, testing plays a crucial role, but it can be challenging to
   conceptualize and execute. Designing systems under the Open MAS paradigm
   poses even greater challenges due to characteristics such as autonomy,
   reactivity, pro-activity, and social abilities. This paper presents
   state-of-the-art research on testing Open MAS. The goal is to ultimately
   provide a new test method that addresses the unique characteristics of
   Open MAS, along with software and efficient test tools that facilitate
   the automation of testing activities for these systems.},
