   AUG 26, 2024},
Organization = {University College Dublin},
Abstract = {In this paper we define two novel design patterns that can be used with
   statecharts-based agent modeling in many real-world domains that call
   for open Multi-agent System architectures. The first pattern is based on
   the well-known factory design pattern, and the second on the composite
   pattern. The applicability of our proposed patterns is demonstrated with
   ASEME, an agent-oriented software engineering methodology that uses
   statecharts for the inter- and intra-agent control models and the
   popular, FIPA standards-compliant, JADE agent platform. We showcase the
   patterns usage through an application for the modern vehicle-to-grid
   (V2G) and grid-to-vehicle (G2V) energy transfer problem domain.},
