Number = {1},
Pages = {133-138},
Month = {JAN},
Abstract = {AI agents are rapidly transforming the software engineering landscape,
   supported by a wave of new frameworks. Our review of the 10 most
   representative general-purpose agentic AI frameworks reveals a maturing
   but fragmented landscape. While some frameworks provide enterprise-ready
   capabilities, most remain immature, with limited memory models, basic
   reasoning, and uneven ecosystem support. Significant improvements are
   needed before these frameworks can enable reliable and large-scale
   adoption in practice.},
