   18-20, 2024},
Abstract = {The MIT Spurdog AUV is a low-cost autonomous underwater vehicle (AUV)
   designed to facilitate research in multi-agent heterogeneous autonomy.
   The core vehicle costs less than \$3,000 USD and utilizes commercially
   available or 3D-printed parts to enable easy reproduction and
   maintenance. Featuring a new Sequential Coupling System for modular
   payload integration, the Spurdog supports rapid reconfiguration and
   multiple modes of manufacture. This paper presents the Spurdog's
   mechanical, electrical, and software architecture, highlighting its
   potential serve as an intermediate platform which bridges the gap
