Month = {FEB},
Abstract = {The development of chatbots is often hindered by high costs and time
   consumption, with existing technologies and frameworks not fully
   addressing the diverse requirements for creating robust conversational
   agents across platforms like WhatsApp. This is a limitation for the
   implementation of these frameworks in a professional environment, thus
   representing both opportunities and complexities. This article presents
   improvements to the Xatkit framework, utilizing Model-Driven Development
   techniques to simplify chatbot development and extend support for
   WhatsApp. Additionally, the integration of the GPT-3 autoregressive
   language model enhances user interaction, offering a more sophisticated
