   BOTSE},
Year = {2025},
Pages = {6-10},
Note = {6th International Workshop on Bots in Software Engineering-BotSE,
   Ottawa, CANADA, APR 27, 2025},
Organization = {Association for Computing Machinery; IEEE Computer Society; Institute of
   Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc},
Abstract = {As Large Language Models (LLMs) are increasingly adopted in software
   engineering, recently in the form of conversational assistants, ensuring
   these technologies align with developers' needs is essential. The
   limitations of traditional human-centered methods for evaluating
   LLM-based tools at scale raise the need for automatic evaluation. In
   this paper, we advocate combining insights from human-computer
   interaction (HCI) and artificial intelligence (AI) research to enable
   human-centered automatic evaluation of LLM-based conversational SE
   assistants. We identify requirements for such evaluation and challenges
   down the road, working towards a framework that ensures these assistants
   are designed and deployed in line with user needs.},
