Note = {35th International Symposium on Software Reliability Engineering,
   Tsukuba, JAPAN, OCT 28-31, 2024},
Abstract = {The future of space exploration lies in cooperative autonomous systems.
   Ensuring their high-integrity remains a challenge. The Robust Software
   Engineering group at NASA Ames Research Center has been developing the
   Troupe project to explore the challenges with developing and assuring
   high-integrity of cooperative autonomous robotic systems. In particular,
   Troupe aims to develop a swarm of autonomous rovers capable of mapping
   unknown terrain, and assure their high-integrity using the advanced V\&V
   tools developed in the group. In this paper, we present the evolution of
   the design of Troupe. We focus on the lessons learned in developing and
   assuring the rover swarm using core Flight System (cFS). In particular,
   we discuss the benefits and challenges in applying model-based
   development to develop the rover swarm.},
